description: More than £6 million a day is lost to internet scammers on average, with 312 instances of online fraud or cyber crime a day over the past two years.

title: Princess of Wales tells young fan that her children got 'lots of lovely things' for Christmas
description: The young fan, named India, was filmed giving the Princess a bouquet of flowers as the Royal Family joined King Charles yesterday on his walkabout outside Sandringham church.

title: Tesla is set to have its worst year EVER as car firm's share price slumps by 70% in 13 months
description: Tesla shares are down 64% for the year, potentially marking their worst annual performance since going public in 2010. Musk sold $2.58 billion worth of Tesla stock last week.

title: NHS bosses spend £65million a year on prescriptions for items such as bread and SHAMPOO
description: Health chiefs had promised to cut down on wasteful prescriptions in 2018 but the amount spent on providing household goods has risen by nearly half since before the pandemic.

title: NHS bosses want interview panels to justify why they have hired a white person
description: Woke NHS bosses are forcing interview panels to explain why they have hired a white person over someone from an ethnic minority, the Daily Mail can reveal.

title: Another seasonal story from our lovable rogue, to celebrate a centenary of Just William
description: William walked slowly and thoughtfully down the village street. It was the week after Christmas. Henry was still away. Douglas and Ginger were the only two of his friends left in the village.

title: Camilla's guest-edited edition of Country Life becomes biggest-selling issue ever
description: The edition, which featured a photograph of Camilla taken by the Princess of Wales and told of her own strong bond with the UK's natural environment, sold nearly 70,000 copies.

title: Kings County receives Ebenezer Award over woke edict banning Christmas or Hannukah displays
description: King County, which encompasses Seattle, was the recipient of this year's award from the Becket Fund for Religious Liberty due to its 'Guidelines for Holiday Decorations,' the group said in a statement.

title: Four-year-old strolls into Santa's grotto unaided a year after cancer confined her to a wheelchair
description: After cancer left her in a wheelchair, Yasmin Roper's main wish this Christmas was to be able to walk into Santa's grotto by herself. And last week the four-year-old defied the odds to achieve it.

title: Florida sheriff's deputy fatally shot on Christmas Eve responding to domestic violence suspect
description: Florida sheriff's deputy Cpl. Ray Hamilton was fatally shot by Timothy Price Wiliams, 43, Christmas Eve while he was responding to a domestic violence assault.

title: Firm linked to husband of 'Baroness Bra' Michelle Mone lavishes £10m on Belgravia townhouse
description: Michelle Mone's husband (both pictured) property in Belgravia - one of London's most exclusive areas - was bought in December 2020 by Chester Ventures weeks after it was incorporated.

title: Florida man allegedly beat five-month-old Goldendoodle to death
description: A trial date has been set for the Florida man accused of beating his five-month-old Goldendoodle, 'Buzz Lightyear,' to death.

title: LA pastor foster mom struck and killed by hit-and-run driver while giving out Christmas presents
description: Trina Newman, 61, a dedicated activist and minister, was tragically hit by a car while dropping off presents for local kids at a community center in South Los Angeles.
